A BAITHAK FOR ALL!

LGBTQIA+ identities have long been part of Indian history, where gender and sexuality were fluid. From cross-dressing gods and Bharatanatyam dancers to Sufi qawwalis and prehistoric cave art, same-sex love was once embraced without shame.

Join our baithak at Cafe Saka in Safdarjung Enclave - an indoor Air conditioned venue, as we uncover the rich history of same-sex love in India. Through literature, films, history, and law, we challenge the myth that homosexuality is a Western import.

Date: 21st June, 2025
Time: 11 AM
Duration: 1.5 hours
Walk fee: 1199/- per person
( Incl. Beverage & Refreshment )
Walk leader: Nitika
Location : Cafe Saka, Safdarjung Enclave

🎁 BONUS : Get a chance to win a vouchers worth ₹2500 from @truebrowns

Plan your weekend with Delhinama and DM us now to book your slot

Tickets are non-refundable unless the event is cancelled by the organisers.
